Write a program to reverse of the half right list.


def reverse_half_right(lst):
  mid = len(lst)//2
  if n%2==0:
      mid=mid
  else:
      mid=mid+1
  lst[mid:] = reversed(lst[mid:])

n=int(input()) 
my_list = list(map(int,input().split()))
reverse_half_right(my_list)
print(my_list)


OUTPUT:

5
1 2 3 4 5
[1, 2, 3, 5, 4]




